text:
I just got through the chat losing it over 3 green vs 4 green on the scale, so for those who are still confused let me clarify why it's not 4 greens.

The people who said 4 were too focused on the one scale that was even, with green and purple balancing the yellow. I think what happened is they assumed it was 3(yellow)=1(green)+2(purple). Therefore two purples would be 4 and thus need four greens. However that can't be how it's balanced as proven by the far left set of scales where 3 greens are more than one yellow. If the first assumption were true then that set of scales would be balanced. That means the balanced scale is probably 5=2+3. Green still weighs more than purple (middle scale), and now three greens (being 6) is more than one yellow (being 5) which makes the left scale correct. Now we find that two purples is also 6, so it's three greens.

Hope that helps.

Oh my god, I can't stop laughing about the BIRD UP part during Shogi. Do you remember, Gura, when you played Monster Hunter, and there was this weird raptor-chicken thing that always made chat spam "B-B-B-BIRD UP!" whenever it was on screen? It's that. It's that same silly meme, that I don't think you ever understood, come back to haunt you. The moment you asked "bird up?" it triggered the meme lord in all of chat, and sealed your fate.

BIRD UP!

That aside, this whole stream was lots of fun. VR Gura always feels like unfiltered goofball Gura, which is always hilarious and adorable. Also, it's always a blast when chat gets to be part of stream. Shrimp smort!

Try not to have nightmares about BABY CHESS Goomba. See ya next stream, whatever ends up happening!
